Among the earliest people here in America there were those who were &quot;contrary&quot;  ..those who did things backward!  They ridiculed sacred institutions and the people laughed.  They had sexual identity problem and the people laughed.  They rode their horses backward and the people laughed. They were given a wide berth and were &quot;respected.&quot;  Not respected for good deeds but out of a concern that they were indeed consumed by bad spirits (foul habits and dysfunctional thought processes)!  The people observed them as a standard of what not to do, but kept them at arms length to avoid social contamination and exposure to demonic spirits!  We are fortunate to have a &quot;contrary&quot; in our &quot;No Sweat&quot; lodge! While we laugh at his antics we will remember to thank the Creator that we are not like him!<br>
They were often called, &quot;Winkte,&quot; man who wants to be a woman!<br>
Remember to laugh at him.. but do not let his sickness touch you...remember that he is a welcomed reference point!<br><br>
